[4] Bulgaria: update
Date: Wed 4 Jan 2017 15:42 EET
Source: Focus Information Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2017/01/04/414821/latest-report-on-bird-flu-in-bulgaria-26-outbreaks-in-9-districts-more-than-100000-animals-killed.html


There are 26 bird flu outbreaks on the territory of Bulgaria. They are found in 9 districts, while more than 100 000 animals have been killed so far.

This is the latest report of the Bulgarian Food Safety Agency on the situation around the spreading of bird flu on the territory of the country.

The figures were announced at a sitting of the national operational headquarters for control and tackling of the disease. The headquarters is comprised by representatives of the agency, the Ministry of Agriculture and Food, the Ministry of Interior, the State Agency for National Security.

